cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.CR 

This paper proposes a new model for predictive analytics that combines the linearity of Factorization Machines (FM) with the non-linearity of neural networks. The paper focuses on the application of this model to sparse data, which is a common problem in web applications. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) since the paper deals with predictive tasks and models. The paper also mentions the use of natural language processing techniques, which suggests a possible connection to cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper discusses the importance of security in web applications, which could relate to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
